IMP Tools Privacy Policy
At IMP Tools, we prioritize the privacy and security of our users. This privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our applications and games on Android.
Acceptance of Policy
By using our apps and games, you agree to the terms of this privacy policy. If you do not agree with this policy, please do not use our products.
Information We Collect
Personal Information:
We do not collect, store, or use any personal information while you use our apps and games.
Non-Personal Information:
We may collect non-personal information to improve our services, including but not limited to:
Device information (e.g., IMEI, MAC address)
Operating system version
GPS location
IP address
Usage data (e.g., crash reports, analytics)
Some of our apps may include advertisements from third-party services like Facebook and Google AdMob, which may collect non-personal data for ad targeting purposes. We will clearly mention in play store which apps or games have ads inside.
Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not share your personal information with any third parties, except as required by law or regulation. We may share non-personal data with third-party partners for analytical and advertising purposes.
Permissions
Some of our apps & games may need certain permissions, like internet access, to work properly. You will be asked to allow these permissions when you use the app. If you don’t grant them, the app may not work as intended. IMP Tools does not force anyone to give permissions.
DMCA Compliance
We respect intellectual property rights and expect our users to do the same. If you believe your copyright has been infringed, please submit a DMCA Notice of Alleged Infringement to us.
Advertisement
Privacy Settings
If you find any infringements then kindly contact us with the proof of the copyright, we will surely help you out with your copyrights things.
Content Policy
We actively monitor and remove content that violates our guidelines or applicable laws. If you encounter any such content, please report it to us, we will remove it. Users found violating these guidelines may have their accounts suspended.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We do not explicitly use cookies, but our apps may incorporate third-party libraries that do. You can choose to accept or refuse cookies; however, refusing cookies may limit your access to certain features of our services.
Links to Other Sites
Our apps may contain links to external websites. We do not control these sites and recommend reviewing their privacy policies. We are not responsible for their content or practices.
Children’s Privacy
Our services are not intended minor age users. We do not knowingly or unknowingly collect personal information from minor age users. If we become aware of such information, we will promptly delete it. Parents or guardians should contact us if they believe their child has provided personal information.
Changes to This Policy
This privacy policy may be updated periodically. Any updates done in this privacy policy will be posted on this page. We encourage you to review this policy regularly.
Contact Us
For any queries related to privacy policy please contact us at mailto:
imptools@outlook.com
